b'So the stats show how good Kimmich is when you watch him 90 minutes. He clearly is superior to Pedri, however in certain aspects the youngster is pretty close, like he was with Modric. Nothing to be ashamed of if you ask me.'

b'Now lets go to the final category of dribbling and carrying the ball. Kimmich is a master in passing but also an amazing dribbler. He attempted 42 and completed 28, giving him a percentage of 66.7%. Pedri like with Modric, falls behind with 57.8%.'

b'So the stats show Pedri is more a bit more secure with his passing, however like with Modric, Kimmich completely wins when it comes to keypasses and progressive passing. The Bayern midfielder had an amazing of 92 keypasses and 284(!) progressive passes.'

b'Kimmich gives way more passes but is less effective than Pedri when it comes to completion. Kimmich attempted 2682 passes, completing 2241 of them, giving him a percentage of 83.6%. Pedri has a slightly better percentage of 87.5% like we have seen with the comparison to Modric. https://t.co/nQTFZRyEIV'

b'All in all, you can say Pedri has great stats when you compare it to the veteran and arguably best midfielder in the world that is Luka Modric. He has margin to improve but is in certain things already scary close and not too far behind.'

b'When it comes to progressive carrying, meaning moving the ball towards the opponents goal at least 5 yards, or any carry into the penalty area, Modric also shows his experience: he had 305 of them while Pedri only had 204. Margin to improve! https://t.co/R2lNeIJXAI'
b'Pedri attempted 64 dribbles and completed 37, giving him a percentage of 57.8%. It is still a pretty good percentage but not close to to Modric.'

b'Last but not least, the dribble and progressive stats for both maestros. Both like to dribble but this one is big time for Luka Modric. The former Ballon D\xe2\x80\x99or winner shows his superiority by attempting 94 dribbles, completing 67 of them, giving him a whopping percentage of 71.3%.'

b'The Spanish youngster had 55 succesful tackles from which the team regained possession, while the Croatian had 39. However when pressing it gets more close. Modric applied pressure 525 times and was succesful 143 times, giving him a percentage of 27.2%.'

b'On to the defensive work, both of them have the image of, while being a creative player, also doing a lot of work. And the stats definitely back this theory. Pedri  wins this battle against Modric.'
b'Modric gave 66 keypasses while Pedri gave only 43. A notable number for the 17-18 year old. Modric had 289 progressive passes while Pedri had 151 of them. If you ask me that is pretty good.'

b'Both are pass masters and the stats show it. Pedri attempted 2063 passes and completed 1806 of them, giving him a completion of 87.5%. Modric attempted 3183 passes and completed 2785, giving him, as well, a completion of 87.5%. https://t.co/XB7vgvHpc2'

b'However, Modric shot 20 times on target and Pedri 12 times, which gives Modric 32.8% shot on target percentage and Pedri slightly under that with 32.4%. However both are not per se known for shooting. Lets go to passing.'

b'Both of them played 52 matches, that season with Pedri scoring 4 and assisting 6 times, Modric scored 6 and gave 6 assists. Pretty close. When it comes to shooting it is pretty similar, Modric shoots way more often than Pedri. 61 for the Croat versus 37 of Pedri.'
